        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>A constant value that is used in the threshold calculation formula. Expressed as a rational where the first member of the tuple is the numerator and the second is the denominator. The rational should represent a value between 0 and 1. In substrate it is called <computeroutput>c</computeroutput> In the threshold formula calculation, <computeroutput>1 - <ref refid="d4/dbe/structsgns_1_1primitives_1_1_production_configuration_1a4e8373c55c829b12d9f6df7b4d3c7d7f" kindref="member">leadership_rate</ref></computeroutput> represents the probability of a slot being empty. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
